  "summary": "Rolly Claude informs Lynn that he has consulted Hercule Poirot, who identified a man named Potter as the best friend of Robert André. According to Rolly, Potter confirmed that the deceased man at the Stagg Inn was indeed Robert André. Rolly celebrates this discovery, believing it defeats the \"con artists\" Hunter and his sister. He explains that because Rosaline was not married to Gordon when her first husband was alive, she cannot claim Gordon's money, which means Rolly will receive a quarter of the inheritance. Rolly suggests providing Rosaline with a living allowance, but he expresses contempt for David, accusing him of being a murderer who killed André to prevent blackmail and secure the inheritance.\n\nLynn counters Rolly's timeline by noting that David caught the 9:20 train to London, a fact she knows because he called her from there. Despite her defense, Lynn privately worries that David's strange behavior and haste suggest he may have killed André before catching the train, and she fears he will eventually be hanged.\n\nMeanwhile, David instructs a distressed Rosaline to remain calm and stick to their story: that the dead man was not her husband, Robert André. When Rosaline expresses guilt over taking money that does not belong to them, David uses fear to manipulate her, telling her that only her admission of the truth could lead to his execution. He advises her to act \"a little stupid\" during questioning and informs her that he has hired a criminal lawyer, Guy Thorn, to protect her during the interrogation.",
